    { questionText: "According to linear perspective, how large should an object twice as far away appear compared to an identical object in the foreground?", correctAnswer: "Roughly half the size", options: ["Roughly half the size", "Exactly the same size", "About a quarter of the size", "Twice as large"], explanation: "Objects shrink proportionally to distance, so doubling the distance roughly halves the apparent size.", hint: "Think about a simple proportional relationship between distance and size." }
