    { questionText: "Renaissance painters often reserved brilliant ultramarine blue specifically for which figure in religious artwork?", correctAnswer: "The Virgin Mary", options: ["The Virgin Mary", "Roman emperors", "The artist's own self-portrait", "Angels only"], explanation: "Renaissance painters often reserved brilliant blue specifically for the robes of the Virgin Mary.", hint: "This important religious figure's robes were traditionally painted in the most expensive blue." },
    { questionText: "What cheaper synthetic blue pigment, invented in the early 1700s, made vivid blue far more accessible to artists?", correctAnswer: "Prussian blue", options: ["Prussian blue", "Viridian", "Chrome yellow", "Mauveine"], explanation: "Prussian blue, invented in the early 1700s, made vivid blue far more accessible to artists.", hint: "This pigment's name references a historical European kingdom." },
    { questionText: "What common English phrase reflects blue's well-known association with sadness?", correctAnswer: "Feeling blue", options: ["Feeling blue", "Seeing red", "Green with envy", "Tickled pink"], explanation: "The phrase 'feeling blue' reflects blue's well-known association with sadness in English.", hint: "This phrase directly uses the color's name to describe an emotion." }
